SIMPLE: pompon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pompon
<hw>Pom"pon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Any trifling ornament for a woman's dress or bonnet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A tuft or ball of wool, or the
like, sometimes worn by soldiers on the front of the hat (such as a
shako), instead of a feather.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A hardy garden chrysanthemum having
buttonlike heads of flowers.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any of several
dwarf varieties of the Provence rose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>the globe-shaped flower head characteristic of
certain plants such as dahlias and chrysanthemums.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>a ball-shaped cluster of ribbons or streamers held
in the hand and waved by some cheerleaders at team sports contests. See
<er>pompom girl</er>. Called also <altname>pompom</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pomposity</ent>⟦br⟧
